.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/13/1110451592_0:160:3072:1888_640x0_80_0_0_dabed1f8a3604574acbec1c2061eafa6.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/13/1110451592_0:160:3072:1888_1280x0_80_0_0_198e72b5425a4c486873c6c283440b90.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/13/1110451592_0:160:3072:1888_1920x0_80_0_0_1c581b7242d3013266e71c2592a112f7.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © 美联社照片 / Eugene Hoshiko </div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">据华盛顿（人造卫星）网报道：拜登政府的一位高级官员告诉记者，美国债务上限的情况以及美国政府违约的可能性削弱了七国集团（G7）国家继续塑造世界的能力记者。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">这位官员指出，债务上限边缘政策削弱了美国在世界上的领导地位和美国金融体系在全球经济中的持续中心地位，因为它质疑了财政部的全部信心和信用。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"><p> “所有这些事情都削弱了美国的领导能力，削弱了我们执行诸如实施我们明天将实施的那种严厉制裁之类的事情的能力，这些制裁的前提是美国金融体系的持续中心地位，结果将破坏七国集团真正继续塑造世界并为其本国公民以及更广泛的世界公民提供服务的能力，”这位官员说。 </p></div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110451884" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230519/us-debt-ceiling-issue-to-undermine-g7-capacity-in-shaping-world---biden-official-1110451884.html?share-block=1110451886" data-title="&amp;quot;All of those things reduce America&amp;#x27;s capacity to lead, reduce our ability to do things like deliver tough sanctions of the kind that we will deliver tomorrow, which are predicated on that ongoing centrality of the US financial system and will, as a result,  undermine the capacity of the G7 to really continue shaping the world and deliver for its own citizens, but also citizens of the world more broadly,&amp;quot; the official said."></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">美国总统拜登和共和党议员目前正在进行谈判，以期在美国政府最早于 6 月面临违约风险之前达成提高债务上限的协议。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">债务上限谈判已持续数月，但仅在最近几周才愈演愈烈，双方似乎都在为即将达成的协议采取一些行动；但是，尚未得到官方确认。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">自 1 月以来，美国一直在“非常措施”下运作，财政部长珍妮特耶伦表示，紧急措施最早将于 6 月 1 日开始动摇。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="vrez"><div class="article__vrez"><div class="article__vrez-text"><p>拜登将参加本周末在日本举行的七国集团领导人峰会，但鉴于美国债务上限危机，他推迟了对澳大利亚和巴布亚新几内亚的访问。</p><p>拜登的日本之行本应是对印太地区更广泛访问的一部分，其中包括在巴布亚新几内亚和澳大利亚的停留。</p></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">拜登政府官员进一步告诉记者，拜登此行将看到美国总司令重申美国对核不扩散的承诺，以及对中华人民共和国表现出“历史性程度的团结”。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “我确实认为你会再次看到七国集团在一系列问题上的历史性团结，但重要的是，在中华人民共和国方面也是如此，”当被问及公报的措辞时，这位官员表示中国。 </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110451884" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230519/us-debt-ceiling-issue-to-undermine-g7-capacity-in-shaping-world---biden-official-1110451884.html?share-block=1110451892" data-title="&quot;I do think what you will see is, again, a historic degree of unity across the G7, across a range of issues but importantly, on the People's Republic of China, as well,&quot; the official said when asked about the communique's language regarding China."></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">还指出，除了将实体列入黑名单之外，七国集团还将利用这个机会公布 300 多项与俄罗斯相关的制裁措施。其中一些已经<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230519/uks-prime-minister-bans-imports-of-russian-diamonds-copper-aluminium--nickel-1110451750.html" target="_blank">公布</a>。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> “美国将推出我们自己的一揽子计划......除其他外，这涉及广泛限制对战场至关重要的商品类别，并通过增加他们被列入商业黑名单，”该官员告诉记者。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"><strong>这位官员说，美国还将宣布对欧洲、中东和亚洲的个人、实体、船只和飞机实施“超过 300 项美国制裁”，目标是规避制裁和其他帮助支持俄罗斯在乌克兰行动的行为者。</strong> </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text">这位官员补充说：“我们还将把制裁权限扩大到俄罗斯经济中对其军事工业综合体至关重要的其他部门，并实施新的禁令，以防止俄罗斯从我们的服务中获益。” </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110451884" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230519/us-debt-ceiling-issue-to-undermine-g7-capacity-in-shaping-world---biden-official-1110451884.html?share-block=1110451897" data-title="&quot;We’ll also expand our sanctions authorities to additional sectors of the Russian economy key to its military industrial complex and impose new bans to prevent Russia from benefiting from our services,&quot; the official added."></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">然而，据这位不愿透露姓名的高级官员称，制裁并不是所有官员都会讨论的问题，他进一步表示各方将采取措施减少对俄罗斯能源的依赖并在经济上孤立俄罗斯。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">此外，这位官员表示，领导人将重申他们对维持俄罗斯石油价格上限的承诺，包括通过有效的监督执法，同时避免溢出效应和维护全球能源安全。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="vrez"><div class="article__vrez"><div class="article__vrez-text"><p> G7 会议将于 5 月 19 日至 21 日举行，届时将有大批全球领导人和政要齐聚广岛，广岛已经出现了抗议活动的团体。</p></div></div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 19 May 2023 02:51:12 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230519/us-debt-ceiling-issue-to-undermine-g7-capacity-in-shaping-world---biden-official-1110451884.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230519/us-debt-ceiling-issue-to-undermine-g7-capacity-in-shaping-world---biden-official-1110451884.html<category>经济</category><category>G7</category><category>中华人民共和国</category><category>俄罗斯</category><category>中国</category><category>珍妮特·耶伦</category><category>乔·拜登</category><category>制裁</category><category>俄罗斯经济受到制裁</category><category>美国债务上限危机</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[UK's Prime Minister Bans Imports of Russian Diamonds, Copper, Aluminium & Nickel - Report]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110451750" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/15635/62/156356295_0:0:500:375_1440x900_80_0_1_9a6a35ba5faa4a2df491215412a0012f.jpg?source-sid=" data-photoview-image-id="156356294" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230519/uks-prime-minister-bans-imports-of-russian-diamonds-copper-aluminium--nickel-1110451750.html?share-img=156356294"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© www.flickr.com 作者：Swamibu</span><span class="photoview__desc-text">钻石</span></div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="" alt="diamonds - Sputnik International, 1920, 19.05.2023" title="钻石" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/15635/62/156356295_0:47:500:328_1920x0_80_0_0_a2c3e02fa8acf1147138e2c031ab1576.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/15635/62/156356295_0:47:500:328_640x0_80_0_0_e9a78d77128b805a6da2480184081bba.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/15635/62/156356295_0:47:500:328_1280x0_80_0_0_cb6782b3b43bd1b3a1c073e030d9315b.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/15635/62/156356295_0:47:500:328_1920x0_80_0_0_a2c3e02fa8acf1147138e2c031ab1576.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © www.flickr.com 作者：Swamibu </div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">据莫斯科（人造卫星）网报道：英国首相里希·苏纳克周四宣布，对从俄罗斯进口钻石、铜、铝和镍实行禁运。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">英国媒体报道称，除了制裁涉及俄罗斯军事工业部门的 86 名个人和实体外，制裁还包括冻结价值 40 亿美元的钻石出口市场。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">苏纳克目前正在日本广岛参加七国集团（G7）峰会。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">欧洲理事会主席查尔斯·米歇尔周五表示，欧盟正计划限制俄罗斯钻石的贸易。 “我们将限制俄罗斯钻石的贸易，”米歇尔在 G7 领导人齐聚日本广岛参加峰会时说，法国媒体援引这一消息。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> G7 峰会将于 5 月 19 日至 21 日在广岛举行，将重点讨论乌克兰冲突、经济安全、绿色投资和印太地区的发展。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">印度、澳大利亚、巴西、韩国、越南、印度尼西亚、科摩罗、库克群岛等国领导人以及联合国、世界银行、和世界卫生组织。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 19 May 2023 02:31:44 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230519/uks-prime-minister-bans-imports-of-russian-diamonds-copper-aluminium--nickel-1110451750.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230519/uks-prime-minister-bans-imports-of-russian-diamonds-copper-aluminium--nickel-1110451750.html<category>世界</category><category>俄罗斯</category><category>欧盟 (EU)</category><category>里士苏纳克</category><category>查尔斯·米歇尔</category><category>禁运</category><category>钻石</category><category>铜</category><category>铝</category><category>镍</category><category>G7峰会</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Perseverance Rover Sends First Images of Mars' Belva Crater]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110450813" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/13/1110450650_0:0:9999:1324_1440x900_80_0_1_8def47f12862122615ec29f1e7cc9790.jpg?source-sid=nasa" data-photoview-image-id="1110450632" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230519/perseverance-rover-sends-first-images-of-mars-belva-crater-1110450813.html?share-img=1110450632"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">©<a href="http://www.nasa.gov/" title="美国宇航局">美国宇航局</a>。 <a href="https://mars.nasa.gov/resources/27471/perseverance-takes-in-view-at-belva-crater/" title="JPL-加州理工学院/ASU/MSSS">JPL-Caltech/ASU/MSSS</a></span> <span class="photoview__desc-text">Mars Belva Crater by Perseverance。</span> </div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="nasa" alt="Mars Belva Crater by Perseverance. - Sputnik International, 1920, 19.05.2023" title="毅力号火星贝尔瓦陨石坑。" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/13/1110450650_3823:0:6177:1324_1920x0_80_0_0_8757104aa20d11dfe207fdf12d0af90c.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/13/1110450650_3823:0:6177:1324_640x0_80_0_0_336c1d03cfa2670e5fef12c2c7d4431f.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/13/1110450650_3823:0:6177:1324_1280x0_80_0_0_565189d638afe76cf72d968396575d72.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/13/1110450650_3823:0:6177:1324_1920x0_80_0_0_8757104aa20d11dfe207fdf12d0af90c.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> ©<a href="http://www.nasa.gov/" title="美国宇航局">美国宇航局</a>。 <a href="https://mars.nasa.gov/resources/27471/perseverance-takes-in-view-at-belva-crater/" title="JPL-加州理工学院/ASU/MSSS">JPL-加州理工学院/ASU/MSSS</a> </div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__author"><div class="article__author-item"><div class="article__author-wrapper"><div class="article__author-info"><div class="article__author-name">叶戈尔·沙波瓦洛夫</div><div class="article__author-links"><a class="m-color-main" href="https://sputniknews.com/author_shapovalov_egor/" title="所有材料">所有材料</a><a data-modal-open="feedback_author" href="mailto:e.shapovalov@sputniknews.com" title="写给作者">写给作者</a></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">NASA 的毅力号火星探测器使用其 Mastcam-Z 仪器拍摄了一幅马赛克图像，为了解 Jezero 陨石坑的内部提供了宝贵的见解。这些照片是在火星车位于 Jezero Crater 内的一个大型撞击坑附近时拍摄的。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">美国宇航局最新发布的镜头让我们得以一瞥火星的贝尔瓦陨石坑，更具体地说是陨石坑本身的内部结构。共有 152 张图像拼接在一起组成图像。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">这些图像是在任务的第 772 个火星日 4 月 22 日拍摄的，揭示了裸露的基岩和陡峭向下倾斜的沉积层。它还进一步证实了早期关于存在大型火星沙洲的建议，该沙洲是在数十亿年前形成的，当时一条河道流入曾经存在于 Jezero 陨石坑中的湖泊。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “火星漫游者的任务通常最终会在漫游者的直接工作空间中以小而平坦的方式探索基岩，”南加州美国宇航局喷气推进实验室的毅力计划副项目科学家凯蒂斯塔克摩根说。 “这就是为什么我们的科学团队如此热衷于对 Belva 进行成像和研究。撞击坑可以提供宏伟的视野和垂直切割，以我们通常不会体验到的视角和规模为这些岩石的起源提供重要线索。” </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110450813" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230519/perseverance-rover-sends-first-images-of-mars-belva-crater-1110450813.html?share-block=1110450928" data-title="&quot;Mars rover missions usually end up exploring bedrock in small, flat exposures in the immediate workspace of the rover,&quot; said Katie Stack Morgan, deputy project scientist of Perseverance at NASA’s Jet Propulsion Laboratory in Southern California. &quot;That’s why our science team was so keen to image and study Belva. Impact craters can offer grand views and vertical cuts that provide important clues to the origin of these rocks with a perspective and at a scale that we don’t usually experience.&quot;"></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">火星车的科学团队认为，前景中的大石头可能是陨石撞击暴露的基岩残余物，或者是被古老的河流系统输送到陨石坑中的残余物。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">为了帮助分析地质特征，该任务还创建了一个 3D 版本的马赛克，称为浮雕。这种可视化使科学家能够更好地了解火山口壁露头之间的关系，并提供身临其境的体验。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “浮雕可以帮助我们形象化火山口壁露头之间的地质关系，”斯塔克说。 “但它也提供了一个简单地欣赏美景的机会。当我通过红蓝色 3D 眼镜观看这幅马赛克时，我仿佛置身于贝尔瓦的西部边缘，我想知道未来的宇航员如果是的话会怎么想站在毅力号拍摄这张照片时曾经站过的地方。” </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110450813" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230519/perseverance-rover-sends-first-images-of-mars-belva-crater-1110450813.html?share-block=1110450932" data-title="&quot;An anaglyph can help us visualize the geologic relationships between the crater wall outcrops,&quot; said Stack. &quot;But it also provides an opportunity to simply enjoy an awesome view. When I look at this mosaic through red-blue 3D glasses, I’m transported to the western rim of Belva, and I wonder what future astronauts would be thinking if they were to stand where Perseverance once stood when it took this shot.&quot;"></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">毅力号的主要目标是天体生物学，包括寻找古代微生物生命的迹象。火星车将继续研究火星的地质和过去的气候，为人类探索和收集可能含有微生物生命证据的样本铺平道路。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="social"><iframe src="https://mars.nasa.gov/maps/location/?mission=M20&amp;site=NOW" width="800" height="450" scrolling="no" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">未来的任务将与欧洲航天局 (ESA) 合作，取回这些样本并将<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20221002/secure-containment-against-superbug-challenges-nasa-faces-over-mission-to-return-martian-samples-1101441500.html" target="_blank">它们带回</a>地球进行详细分析。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> Mars 2020 Perseverance 任务与 NASA 的月球到火星探索方法保持一致，其中包括 Artemis 登月任务，为未来的人类火星任务做准备。由加州理工学院为 NASA 管理的喷气推进实验室 (JPL) 建造并运营了恒心号漫游车。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 19 May 2023 01:37:51 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230519/perseverance-rover-sends-first-images-of-mars-belva-crater-1110450813.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230519/perseverance-rover-sends-first-images-of-mars-belva-crater-1110450813.html<category>超越政治</category><category>科学与技术</category><category>火星</category><category>美国宇航局</category><category>毅力</category><category>空间</category><category>太空探索</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Report: US May Be Able to Train Ukrainian Pilots to Fly F-16s in Just 4 Months]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110451049" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/02/0e/1107430400_0:0:3109:2047_1440x900_80_0_1_4760be1f161d08da8834ee8e30849e4f.jpg?source-sid=" data-photoview-image-id="1107430382" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230519/report-us-may-be-able-to-train-ukrainian-pilots-to-fly-f-16s-in-just-4-months-1110451049.html?share-img=1107430382"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© <a href="https://www.dvidshub.net/image/5384624/f-16-fighting-falcon-fires-missle" title="高级飞行员约书亚霍斯金斯">高级飞行员 Joshua Hoskins</a></span><span class="photoview__desc-text">一架分配给第 85 测试评估中队的 F-16C 战隼在佛罗里达州埃格林空军基地附近的测试范围内发射 AIM-120 先进中程空对空导弹或 AMRAAM，3 月 19 日, 2019.</span> </div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="" alt="An F-16C Fighting Falcon assigned to the 85th Test Evaluation Squadron shoots an AIM-120 Advanced Medium-Range Air-to-Air Missile, or AMRAAM over testing ranges near Eglin Air Force Base, Fla., March 19, 2019. - Sputnik International, 1920, 19.05.2023" title="2019 年 3 月 19 日，分配给第 85 测试评估中队的 F-16C 战隼在佛罗里达州埃格林空军基地附近的测试范围内发射 AIM-120 先进中程空对空导弹或 AMRAAM。" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/02/0e/1107430400_0:149:3109:1898_1920x0_80_0_0_9b67f492985748d9e2ffee71d760d810.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/02/0e/1107430400_0:149:3109:1898_640x0_80_0_0_c160a6e2375fb82b4a3e33780aa822cc.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/02/0e/1107430400_0:149:3109:1898_1280x0_80_0_0_06a3e985a5341e5982ebcad5d1c27f58.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/02/0e/1107430400_0:149:3109:1898_1920x0_80_0_0_9b67f492985748d9e2ffee71d760d810.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © <a href="https://www.dvidshub.net/image/5384624/f-16-fighting-falcon-fires-missle" title="高级飞行员约书亚霍斯金斯">高级飞行员约书亚霍斯金斯</a></div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">据华盛顿（人造卫星）网报道：美国媒体周四援引美国空军文件报道称，美国训练乌克兰飞行员操作美制战斗机所需的时间可能比之前想象的要少得多。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">这些文件包含今年 2 月和 3 月在亚利桑那州图森空军基地进行的详细评估，在那里，具有飞行 Su-27 和 MiG-29 经验但没有任何 F16 经验的乌克兰飞行员在模拟器中进行了测试，并由合格的空军进行了评估力教官。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">报告称，在评估过程中，这两名乌克兰飞行员仅经过短暂的熟悉，没有经过正式培训，就能够在模拟环境中执行复杂的操作。其中一些演习需要非常专业的技能，包括在模拟发动机失效后降落飞机和执行模拟攻击。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “鉴于乌克兰空军飞行员目前展示的技能组合......四个月是一个现实的训练时间表，”报告中援引这些文件的话说。 </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110451049" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230519/report-us-may-be-able-to-train-ukrainian-pilots-to-fly-f-16s-in-just-4-months-1110451049.html?share-block=1110451052" data-title="&quot;Given the current skill set demonstrated by the Ukrainian Air Force pilot ... four months is a realistic training timeline,” the documents were quoted as saying in the report. "></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">报告补充说，这与负责政策的前国防部副部长科林卡尔 (Colin Kahl) 在 2 月份在国会委员会面前声称训练乌克兰飞行员驾驶 F-16 战斗机所需的 18 个月相比有了很大的转变。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"><strong>乌克兰飞行员面临的最大障碍之一是 F-16 以英语显示信息，尽管飞行员在评估期间表现出了能力方面的进步。</strong></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">周四揭露消息之际，有报道详细说明五角大楼犯了一个严重的会计错误，并设法为乌克兰找到了 30 亿美元的武器。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">国防部副新闻秘书萨布丽娜·辛格周四向卫星通讯社证实，该部门发现乌克兰的设备估值存在不一致，当时使用“重置成本”而不是“账面净值”导致高估了从美国库存中提取的设备的价值。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “在我们对总统缩编计划的定期监督过程中，该部门发现乌克兰的设备估值存在不一致。在某些情况下，使用的是“重置成本”而不是“账面净值”，因此高估了从美国库存中提取的设备的价值，”辛格在一份声明中说。 </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110451049" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230519/report-us-may-be-able-to-train-ukrainian-pilots-to-fly-f-16s-in-just-4-months-1110451049.html?share-block=1110451058" data-title="“During our regular oversight process of presidential drawdown packages, the Department discovered inconsistencies in equipment valuation for Ukraine. In some cases, ‘replacement cost’ rather than ‘net book value’ was used, therefore overestimating the value of the equipment drawn down from US stocks,” Singh said in a statement."></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">声明补充说，会计错误既没有限制美国对乌克兰的支持，也没有影响其向战场输送能力的能力。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 19 May 2023 01:19:15 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230519/report-us-may-be-able-to-train-ukrainian-pilots-to-fly-f-16s-in-just-4-months-1110451049.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230519/report-us-may-be-able-to-train-ukrainian-pilots-to-fly-f-16s-in-just-4-months-1110451049.html<category>军队</category><category>歼16</category><category>乌克兰</category><category>美国空军</category><category>美国军事援助</category><category>军事援助</category><category>五角大楼监察长</category><category>会计错误</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Ukraine Planning to Break Through Flanks in Artyomovsk to Curtail Russia's Advance - DPR Head]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110450085" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e6/09/15/1101036220_0:0:3072:2048_1440x900_80_0_1_d87cb5fb737d46b3fcbd0ae6bf70c006.jpg?source-sid=rian_photo" data-photoview-image-id="1101036203" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230519/ukraine-planning-to-break-through-flanks-in-artyomovsk-to-curtail-russias-advance---dpr-head-1110450085.html?share-img=1101036203"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© Sputnik / Viktor Antonyuk</span><span class="photoview__desc-text">俄罗斯私人军事公司瓦格纳集团的一名军人在乌克兰阵地用 122 毫米 D30 榴弹炮射击，俄罗斯在乌克兰的军事行动仍在继续，在顿涅茨克人民共和国巴赫穆特郊区</span></div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="rian_photo" alt="A serviceman of Russian private military company Wagner Group shoots from a 122 mm D30 howitzer at the Ukrainian positions, as Russia's military operation in Ukraine continues, in the suburbs of Bakhmut, Donetsk People's Republic - Sputnik International, 1920, 19.05.2023" title="俄罗斯私营军事公司瓦格纳集团的一名军人在乌克兰阵地用 122 毫米 D30 榴弹炮射击，俄罗斯在乌克兰的军事行动仍在继续，在顿涅茨克人民共和国巴赫穆特郊区" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e6/09/15/1101036220_0:230:3072:1958_1920x0_80_0_0_1b7603e4a4e3772112e9a800c4ea2e9c.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e6/09/15/1101036220_0:230:3072:1958_640x0_80_0_0_b99ee88add512589a0d18a4007805285.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e6/09/15/1101036220_0:230:3072:1958_1280x0_80_0_0_e0ed9603dbde313c1fd3731a9dce1969.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e6/09/15/1101036220_0:230:3072:1958_1920x0_80_0_0_1b7603e4a4e3772112e9a800c4ea2e9c.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © Sputnik / Viktor Antonyuk</div> / </div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">俄罗斯喀山（人造卫星）网：乌克兰军队蓄意计划突破阿尔乔莫夫斯克市的侧翼，使俄罗斯军队在该市的推进复杂化，但正在采取“详尽措施”来阻止它，代理负责人丹尼斯·普希林 (Denis Pushilin)顿涅茨克人民共和国（DPR）周五告诉人造卫星。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> “敌人现在正蓄意突破侧翼，为阿尔乔莫夫斯克本身和城里的人创造困难条件。因此，当然，正在采取彻底的措施，”他说。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">普希林最近告诉俄罗斯卫星通讯社，阿尔乔莫夫斯克侧翼的情况正在好转，侧翼的增援已经证明是有效的。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">这位官员还详细说明，基辅试图用来为阿尔乔莫夫斯克的部队提供补给的恰西夫亚尔市和阿尔乔莫夫斯克市之间的道路仍然很复杂，但处于俄罗斯军方的火力控制之下。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “[路上的情况]很复杂，但道路在我们部队的火力控制下，”普希林说。 “敌人没有畅通无阻的道路。” </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110450085" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230519/ukraine-planning-to-break-through-flanks-in-artyomovsk-to-curtail-russias-advance---dpr-head-1110450085.html?share-block=1110450587" data-title="&quot;[The situation on the road] is complicated, but the road is under fire control of our units,&quot; Pushilin said. &quot;The enemy has no unimpeded pass down the road.&quot;"></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">俄罗斯国防部 5 月 5 日表示，乌克兰军方曾试图用它为阿尔乔莫夫斯克的士兵提供弹药并部署更多部队，但恰西夫亚尔附近的一座桥已被摧毁。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> Psuhilin 的顾问 Yan Gagin 早些时候说，大量乌克兰军队和装备集中在 Chasiv Yar 本身。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 19 May 2023 00:21:09 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230519/ukraine-planning-to-break-through-flanks-in-artyomovsk-to-curtail-russias-advance---dpr-head-1110450085.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230519/ukraine-planning-to-break-through-flanks-in-artyomovsk-to-curtail-russias-advance---dpr-head-1110450085.html<category>俄罗斯在乌克兰的特别行动</category><category>丹尼斯·普希林</category><category>俄罗斯</category><category>乌克兰</category><category>民主共和国</category><category>乌克兰危机</category><category>士兵</category><category>顿涅茨克人民共和国</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Wisconsin Issues Air Quality Warning Amid Raging Wildfires in Canada]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110449522" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/103915/33/1039153303_0:0:1813:1000_1440x900_80_0_1_2d703bf321a30bbd92718e57b870ad8e.png?source-sid=" data-photoview-image-id="1039153302" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230518/wisconsin-issues-air-quality-warning-amid-raging-wildfires-in-canada-1110449522.html?share-img=1039153302"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© <a href="https://youtu.be/ieTQvIdG-Vo" title="YouTube/GlobalLeaks 新闻">YouTube/GlobalLeaks News</a></span><span class="photoview__desc-text">加拿大无法阻止巨大的野火烧毁艾伯塔省的城镇</span></div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="" alt="Canada Can’t Stop Enormous Wildfires Burning Down Towns Across Alberta - Sputnik International, 1920, 18.05.2023" title="加拿大无法阻止巨大的野火烧毁艾伯塔省的城镇" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/103915/33/1039153303_18:0:1796:1000_1920x0_80_0_0_e418b56f25240cbfdcc845b07c942d83.png" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/103915/33/1039153303_18:0:1796:1000_640x0_80_0_0_502e8a354a1a4fdcb83c4518d30df114.png 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/103915/33/1039153303_18:0:1796:1000_1280x0_80_0_0_d463f949aa214a432cc1140f6223f14f.png 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/103915/33/1039153303_18:0:1796:1000_1920x0_80_0_0_e418b56f25240cbfdcc845b07c942d83.png 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © <a href="https://youtu.be/ieTQvIdG-Vo" title="YouTube/GlobalLeaks 新闻">YouTube/GlobalLeaks 新闻</a></div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__author"><div class="article__author-item"><div class="article__author-wrapper"><div class="article__author-info"><div class="article__author-name">叶戈尔·沙波瓦洛夫</div><div class="article__author-links"><a class="m-color-main" href="https://sputniknews.com/author_shapovalov_egor/" title="所有材料">所有材料</a><a data-modal-open="feedback_author" href="mailto:e.shapovalov@sputniknews.com" title="写给作者">写给作者</a></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">加拿大西部省份（不列颠哥伦比亚省、阿尔伯塔省、萨斯喀彻温省）正在遭受灾难性的森林大火。目前的情况不仅对公民的健康构成威胁，而且对这些地区的经济活动构成威胁。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">威斯康星州自然资源部已对该州大部分地区发布空气质量咨询，以应对加拿大南部持续的野火。该建议将于周四午夜生效，并将持续到周五。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">该警告延伸到威斯康星州北部地区之外，这些地区最近几天已经出现雾霾天气。它现在包括该州的西南部、中南部和东部地区，包括密尔沃基。随着北方空气继续南下，西部地区也有可能受到影响。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">美国国家气象局目前预测，从午夜开始，源自加拿大的野火烟雾将开始从西北向东南移动到威斯康星州南部和东部。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">预计颗粒物的浓度有时会迅速上升，但随着更清洁的空气进入该地区，浓度会逐渐下降。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"><strong>在高峰时段，空气质量指数预计将达到“对敏感人群不健康”的水平。气象局建议这些群体中的个人在这段时间内限制户外体育活动。</strong></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="h2"><h2 class="article__h2">石油、天然气和求助</h2></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">美国媒体援引能源报道称，由于有消息称日产量约为 270 万桶的油砂田持续受到威胁，天然气生产基地也面临危险，因此主要参与者已联合减产至少 240,000 桶/日咨询公司 Rystad Energy。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">加拿大已请求国际社会帮助应对该国西部的大规模森林火灾。艾伯塔省正在遭受火灾，超过 50 万公顷的森林和草原已经被毁。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “艾伯塔省的局势仍然非常令人担忧和危险，”渥太华公共安全部长比尔布莱尔说，因为加拿大政府呼吁外国帮助。 </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110449522" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230518/wisconsin-issues-air-quality-warning-amid-raging-wildfires-in-canada-1110449522.html?share-block=1110449531" data-title="&quot;The situation in Alberta remains very worrying and dangerous,&quot; said Ottawa Public Safety Secretary Bill Blair, as the Canadian government appealed for foreign help."></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">据媒体报道，来自加拿大各地的约 2,500 名消防员和 400 名士兵已被派往艾伯塔省扑灭大火，但到目前为止，已有 27 起火灾失控。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 18 May 2023 23:08:03 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230518/wisconsin-issues-air-quality-warning-amid-raging-wildfires-in-canada-1110449522.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230518/wisconsin-issues-air-quality-warning-amid-raging-wildfires-in-canada-1110449522.html<category>美洲</category><category>加拿大</category><category>国家气象局</category><category>艾伯塔省</category><category>野火</category><category>抽烟</category></item></channel></rss>